        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Geological Society of London | Somerset House.</placeName>
                    <date>20<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. Dec<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. 1838</date>
                    <salute>Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am requested by the Geological Society to express their thanks for the donation of “Proceedings of the American Philosophical Society N<hi rend="superscript">os</hi>. 1 2 &amp; 3. Vol. 1. and to assure you that the Society are much honored by this mark of consideration</p>
<p>I have the honor to be | Sir, | Your most obedient | and very humble Servant | Chas. Darwin | Secretary <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> To | The Secretary of the | American Philosophical Society</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
    
        
